Hi,

I'm looking to add a new element to a list within the payload of a specific point in my collection, without needing to fetch the entire list first and then re-upload it.

For example, I currently send the following PUT request to update the points:

`
PUT /collections/tests/points
{
    "points": [
        {
            "id": 1,
            "payload": {"data": ["a", "b"]},
            "vector": [0.9, 0.1, 0.1]
        }
    ]
}`
The expected result would be:

`
{
    "id": 1,
    "payload": {"data": ["a", "b", "c"]},
    "vector": [0.9, 0.1, 0.1]
}`
I want to append a new element to the payload field of a specific point, but I don't want to fetch the entire list first, modify it, and then upload it again one by one. This process seems inefficient, especially when dealing with a large number of points.

Is there an alternative method to directly append an element to the payload of a point, ensuring that the lists do not have identical elements?

